The Chairman of Oto-Awori Council in Lagos State, Prince Musibau Adekunle Asafa, has sworn-in new supervisors and special advisers that will assist in the day-to-day running of his government. During the inauguration, he reiterated his administration’s commitment to delivering the basic amenities to residents. He noted that the activities of government, most especially at this level, is enormous while indicating the essence of appointing like-minds who will foster effective and efficient governance. However, he charged the appointees to put in their best to raise the bar so that people will continue to enjoy the dividends of democracy. “The task ahead is enormous; our duty is to serve the people without any excuse.  I want you to lead by example and ensure we meet our primary goals”, he stipulated.   ‘How OPL 245 was transferred’     Stakeholders in disability sector for training     NNPC subsidiary NETCO posts N4.31b profit   You will recall that the Vice Chairman, Abdulkareem Abiodin Azeez, was elected and sworn in by the Governor of Lagos State in July last year and he is to supervise the Department of Works . Other appointees are: Fasasi Olalekan Abu as the Secretary to the Local Government, Mumuni Kabiru Olabisi, Supervisor for Agriculture and Social Services, Falade Nathaniel Ibukun, Supervisor for Budget and Planning, Taiwo Bisiriyu, Supervisor for Health, Anomo Ashiribo Aishat, Supervisor for Women Affairs and Poverty Alleviation, Ajose Ezekiel Tekobo, Supervisor for Revenue and Special Duties, Kasali Hassan Adedayo, Supervisor for Education. Others include: Jimoh Rahmon Orelope, Special Adviser on Environment and Ishau Jubril, Special Adviser on Political and Chieftaincy matters. Responding on behalf of the appointees, the Secretary, Fasasi Abu, not to disappoint the Chairman in the discharge of their duties.